{"type": "article", "id": 1468, "title": "如何像个意大利人？", "description": "", "date": "2014-07-15T08:25:00Z", "super_tag": null, "tags": [{"id": 9, "name": "意大利"}, {"id": 1729, "name": "手语"}], "category": 12, "author": 13, "comment_count": 1, "praise_count": 4, "image": "img/article/article_show/2016060716502972aL5WDOBdtgNSsq.png", "contents": "\n\n<p>\r\n\t今天推荐一段简短的手语<strong><a href=\"http://www.mrporter.com/journal/journal_issue169/4?cm_sp=homepage-_-allamanov1-_-08-07-14\" target=\"_blank\">视频</a></strong>。据说这个世界上 93% 的沟通都倚赖于非口头语言。而对于意大利人来说，这个数字甚至偏低。意大利语的丰富性之一就在于它不仅仅只是像打字机一样喋喋不休的发音，还有多样的面部表情、手势和其他肢体动作——它们甚至更能生动地表情达意。\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t这样的数百种手语通常用于窃窃私语、凌辱他人或表示拒绝，但有时也用在表达感激和赞美的时刻。\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t这段视频的内容来自于米兰平面设计师 Bruno Munari 在 1958 年完成的一本手册，其中的大部分至今仍在沿用。\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165025iD9IRHvwkqazsyjW.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.546875\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165025zYhiJSxejXodkR2G.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.5484375\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165026qmkJVZweHuaMFS8D.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.546875\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165026ZuHkPXRDSgVdbBlK.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.546875\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/201606071650277lco0HKCnQyGBU9E.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.5421875\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165027f4kAJaSqKO53Tdir.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.5328125\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160607165028rTMyAR6bB27ekZPF.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.546875\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t题图来源：<a href=\"http://www.mrporter.com/journal/journal_issue169/4?cm_sp=homepage-_-allamanov1-_-08-07-14\" target=\"_blank\">Mr. Porter</a> \r\n</p>\n\n\n"}